svg.title: Hohmann transfer orbit.svg - illustration of a Hohmann transfer orbit
svg.desc:
In orbital mechanics, the Hohmann transfer orbit is an orbital maneuver using two engine impulses which, under standard assumptions, move a spacecraft between two coplanar circular orbits. This maneuver was named after Walter Hohmann, the German scientist who published a description of it in 1925.
